properties.name: description
properties.value: A refinery on the far planet Tartarus. The building contains multiple weapons and three bridges over a dangerous pool of lava.

properties.name: description
properties.value: A drone testing facility on Roccalupo planet. A hide and seek arena featuring a wide range of weapons surrounded by a colonnade. Crossing the center is harder due to acid pools.

properties.name: description
properties.value: A defense tower on the first planet that used the 2nd generation of drones. Two concentric areas linked by a teleport system offering multiple sniping options.

properties.name: description
properties.value: Fereydoon's birthplace at the end of the Unification War. A large map with multiple explorable buildings and narrow alleys.

properties.name: description
properties.value: A lost paradise in the desert that hosted our defeat against Fereydoon. Two symmetrical bases in a wide-open area with four rotating armories.

properties.name: description
properties.value: Fereydoon cargo ships rendezvous point around Oculi Asteroid. Four ships with different layout and a standard armory separated by a large zero gravity area.

properties.name: description
properties.value: Argyros capital after the Drone Frenzy lockdown. A stealthy map with wild grass that makes spotting the Players enemies harder.

properties.name: description
properties.value: Fereydoon glory's monument, now abandoned. A mazy and dark map to chase and stab the enemy. Players are equipped with a tracking system. Watch out.

properties.name: description
properties.value: An autonomous tribal settlement in southern Argyros. Mud, tropical ferns, and darkness will slow down and confuse the Players. Find your enemies before they find you.

properties.name: description
properties.value: The first factory of the Drooney project. A labyrinthine ground floor, conveyor belts and flames on the 2nd floor, and powerful weapons and deadly Plasma cannons on the roof.

properties.name: description
properties.value: A massive archaeological site on Argyros. Players will cross slippery frozen floors and insidious tunnels connected by snowy pathways.

properties.name: description
properties.value: One of the PvP VR battlefields for advanced training. A brutal and chaotic arena, with Plasma projectiles and moving weapons in which every single bullet counts.

properties.name: description
properties.value: The seat of the peace congress between the human resistance and the Aliens on the Argyros orbit. Two towers connected by a suspended bridge. Falling out causes the Player death.

properties.name: description
properties.value: A secret research lab on Ledirea, Argyros satellite. A deadly whirl of Plasma defends the map center, but the hard to navigate drifting bridges are the real threat.
